00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:50,327
All of this clamor isn't
accomplishing anything

258
00:12:50,402 --> 00:12:51,960
except upsetting Emotion.

259
00:12:52,204 --> 00:12:53,535
Hey.

260
00:12:55,074 --> 00:12:57,338
Remember when you had the guts
to face problems head on?

261
00:13:00,746 --> 00:13:02,145
So that's it?

262
00:13:02,214 --> 00:13:04,239
You're just going
to walk away?

263
00:13:04,316 --> 00:13:06,011
What happened
to you Heart?

264
00:13:06,085 --> 00:13:07,109
What made you
so weak?

265
00:13:09,221 --> 00:13:10,984
You're weak!

266
00:13:11,056 --> 00:13:15,720
[suspenseful music]

267
00:13:18,531 --> 00:13:20,465
l've heard enough.

268
00:13:22,768 --> 00:13:23,666
Heart!

269
00:13:26,071 --> 00:13:27,663
There is something
missing in all of this.

270
00:13:27,740 --> 00:13:29,469
Like what?

271
00:13:29,542 --> 00:13:31,305
l've heard
from everyone.

272
00:13:31,377 --> 00:13:32,275
Mind will make
his assessment

273
00:13:32,344 --> 00:13:33,743
and we'll plan
a course of action.

274
00:13:33,813 --> 00:13:36,281
Now let's give
him some space.

275
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:40,581
You haven't heard
from everyone.

276
00:13:42,488 --> 00:14:02,638
[suspenseful music]

277
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:22,660
[party noises]
[chatter]

278
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:23,559
The last one.

279
00:14:23,629 --> 00:14:25,460
Here's the present
Daddy got for you.

280
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:27,055
lt's a surprise.

281
00:14:28,601 --> 00:14:29,329
Let's see...

282
00:14:29,401 --> 00:14:31,301
Thank you, Daddy!

283
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:32,735
Can you read it to me?

284
00:14:32,805 --> 00:14:33,669
Why don't we have
Mommy read it?

285
00:14:33,739 --> 00:14:35,468
ls Daddy too tired
to read?

286
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:36,701
No, l just love
watching you read.

287
00:14:39,211 --> 00:14:40,735
Don't forget.

288
00:14:42,114 --> 00:14:43,775
l love you, too.

289
00:14:43,849 --> 00:14:49,446
[music]

290
00:14:49,521 --> 00:14:50,453
(Will)
<i>Heart.</i>

291
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:53,550
Heart.

292
00:14:56,328 --> 00:14:57,090
Heart.

293
00:14:57,162 --> 00:15:00,757
[Swish noise]

294
00:15:02,301 --> 00:15:03,825
Heart.

295
00:15:06,538 --> 00:15:08,165
Heart.

296
00:15:11,543 --> 00:15:12,703
[brick movement]

297
00:15:12,878 --> 00:15:14,778
Heart.

298
00:15:16,548 --> 00:15:17,708
What were you
doing in there?

299
00:15:18,817 --> 00:15:20,682
Nothing.

300
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:21,583
l was just looking.

301
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:27,516
What do you want?

302
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:29,652
After considering
our options,

303
00:15:29,728 --> 00:15:32,288
Mind thinks we need
to start over.

304
00:15:32,364 --> 00:15:34,161
What do you mean start over,
like go back to church?

305
00:15:34,233 --> 00:15:35,564
No.

306
00:15:35,634 --> 00:15:37,727
The job in Connecticut.

307
00:15:37,803 --> 00:15:40,397
And work for Jeff at his
advertisement firm?

308
00:15:40,472 --> 00:15:41,598
No.

309
00:15:41,674 --> 00:15:43,198
He said we had a job
waiting for us

310
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:44,401
anytime we wanted.

311
00:15:44,476 --> 00:15:45,704
He's our old
college roommate.

312
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:47,769
We said a lot of things to
each other we didn't mean.

313
00:15:48,881 --> 00:15:49,779
Hey!

314
00:15:53,218 --> 00:15:54,617
What about
our security?

315
00:15:55,921 --> 00:15:58,355
Heart, think of it
this way.

316
00:15:58,424 --> 00:16:03,384
The only way we'll ever be
happy again is to move.

317
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:04,656
No.

318
00:16:04,730 --> 00:16:06,823
Look, it was so hard
to get the strip syndicated

319
00:16:06,899 --> 00:16:08,264
and look how
it's turned out.

320
00:16:08,334 --> 00:16:09,323
l don't want
to hear this.

321
00:16:09,401 --> 00:16:10,698
Heart,
are you blind!

322
00:16:12,871 --> 00:16:16,307
Amy is miserable.

323
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:21,472
l mean, it's obvious her
feelings have changed toward us.

324
00:16:21,547 --> 00:16:23,481
Because she blames us.

325
00:16:23,549 --> 00:16:25,813
Stress and the guilt
have nearly crippled us.

326
00:16:25,884 --> 00:16:27,545
Just look at you,
Heart.

327
00:16:27,619 --> 00:16:28,483
l can't.

328
00:16:31,256 --> 00:16:32,518
l won't.

329
00:16:32,591 --> 00:16:36,288
Heart, l hate to say it,
but l believe we can trace

330
00:16:36,362 --> 00:16:39,820
all of our problems back to when
we began this journey of faith.

331
00:16:39,898 --> 00:16:41,695
ln the beginning we
studied the Bible

332
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:44,565
and l was convinced
that it was true.

333
00:16:44,636 --> 00:16:46,433
We prayed consistently,

334
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:48,405
and l thought if we got
involved in ministry

335
00:16:48,474 --> 00:16:50,374
we could please God.

336
00:16:50,442 --> 00:16:51,875
But circumstances
have proven

337
00:16:51,944 --> 00:16:55,311
that no matter how much we did,
just the opposite happened.

338
00:16:55,381 --> 00:16:57,542
Mind is right.

339
00:16:57,616 --> 00:16:59,208
We need to start over.

340
00:16:59,551 --> 00:17:01,712
Reboot.

341
00:17:01,787 --> 00:17:04,255
You know like escape.

342
00:17:04,323 --> 00:17:06,689
l mean there's no
creativity here.

343
00:17:06,759 --> 00:17:08,386
We're being stifled.

344
00:17:08,460 --> 00:17:09,449
Mind can't think.

345
00:17:09,528 --> 00:17:10,586
Will can't draw.

346
00:17:10,662 --> 00:17:11,856
And you've lost
your passion.

347
00:17:13,298 --> 00:17:16,995
You've been listening to that
sorry excuse for a judge.

348
00:17:17,269 --> 00:17:19,965
Don't get me started on
Mr. Past-Time.

349
00:17:20,039 --> 00:17:21,336
Whoa.

350
00:17:23,575 --> 00:17:24,906
We've got to get
out of here.

351
00:17:24,977 --> 00:17:25,841
Wait.

352
00:17:28,447 --> 00:17:32,008
You're making decisions based
solely on circumstances.

353
00:17:32,284 --> 00:17:34,809
We need some
spiritual direction.

354
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:39,017
And here comes
the judge.

355
00:17:39,291 --> 00:17:40,349
l heard you down the hall
and it's obvious

356
00:17:40,426 --> 00:17:42,894
that you are not thinking about
the spiritual implications.

357
00:17:42,961 --> 00:17:45,452
How do you know that
this job opportunity

358
00:17:45,531 --> 00:17:49,399
is not some kind of
divine intervention?

359
00:17:49,468 --> 00:17:50,366
What?

360
00:17:52,037 --> 00:17:52,867
No.

361
00:17:52,938 --> 00:17:54,929
Are you
kidding me?

362
00:17:55,007 --> 00:17:57,339
Emotion! l've had
enough of this!

363
00:17:57,409 --> 00:17:57,841
Oh yeah!

364
00:17:57,910 --> 00:17:58,842
l've had enough of you
Conscience! l had enough.

365
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:05,373
[arguing]

366
00:18:05,451 --> 00:18:09,478
[music]

367
00:18:09,555 --> 00:18:11,352
Read it to me again,
Daddy.

368
00:18:11,423 --> 00:18:13,288
(Michael)
<i> Which book honey? </i>

369
00:18:13,358 --> 00:18:13,983
The Good Shepherd.

370
00:18:15,661 --> 00:18:17,629
( Amy) <i>There once</i>
<i>was a good shepherd</i>

371
00:18:17,696 --> 00:18:19,459
who <i>cared</i>
<i>for his sheep.</i>

372
00:18:19,531 --> 00:18:22,932
He <i>watched over them when</i>
i>they  were awake or asleep.</i

373
00:18:23,001 --> 00:18:23,831
Silence!

374
00:18:26,338 --> 00:18:28,738
You are going in
the wrong direction!

375
00:18:28,807 --> 00:18:33,540
My desire is to get things back
to the way they were.

376
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:34,977
When Amy and l
were in love.

377
00:18:35,047 --> 00:18:36,014
Heart.

378
00:18:36,081 --> 00:18:38,549
What you want
is impossible.

379
00:18:38,617 --> 00:18:40,380
lt can never be
like it was.

380
00:18:40,452 --> 00:18:41,612
The sooner you
except that fact

381
00:18:41,687 --> 00:18:43,416
the better we're
all going to be.

382
00:18:43,489 --> 00:18:49,917
Every time Amy looks at us,
she remembers what happened.

383
00:18:49,995 --> 00:18:52,429
There's no way
of overcoming it.

384
00:18:52,498 --> 00:18:55,058
There's no way
of undoing it.

385
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:57,967
Leaving her is the only
solution that makes sense.

386
00:19:01,039 --> 00:19:07,035
lf you won't do it for you,
do it for Amy.

387
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:13,880
l sense the idea
intrigues you.

388
00:19:19,391 --> 00:19:21,359
Heart.

389
00:19:26,765 --> 00:19:28,596
(Heart) What do you
<i>want with me? </i>

390
00:19:29,668 --> 00:19:33,001
l want you to see
what's happening to us.

391
00:19:33,071 --> 00:19:35,596
Why this light is not
as it once was.

392
00:19:35,674 --> 00:19:38,609
You know this reveals
our true condition.

393
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:41,373
Who we really are
or what we've become.

394
00:19:41,446 --> 00:19:42,913
And it never lies.

395
00:19:48,554 --> 00:19:49,782
That's the problem.

396
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:51,379
What?

397
00:19:52,624 --> 00:19:53,386
What do you see?

398
00:20:02,768 --> 00:20:04,895
All l see is me.

399
00:20:04,970 --> 00:20:06,631
Like l said.

400
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:08,605
That's the problem.

401
00:20:08,674 --> 00:20:11,507
The light of life used to shine
through this glass.

402
00:20:11,577 --> 00:20:14,876
But now it's clouded over
by your grief and guilt.

403
00:20:14,947 --> 00:20:17,541
What does that have to do
with winning my wife back.

404
00:20:17,616 --> 00:20:19,777
Heart, examine
yourself.

405
00:20:19,851 --> 00:20:22,945
You're spiritually weak
and this proves it.

406
00:20:26,525 --> 00:20:27,457
l'm trying
to make you see

407
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:29,153
you're in no condition
to win her back.

408
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:30,661
l did it once.

409
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:33,129
And l can do
it again.

410
00:20:39,571 --> 00:20:40,469
l'm taking off.

411
00:20:42,007 --> 00:20:43,133
Ok.

412
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:45,640
You ok?

413
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:49,641
(Mind) She sure
<i>is beautiful.</i>

414
00:20:49,715 --> 00:20:52,183
(Emotion) Do l have to remind
<i> you that she hates us? </i>

415
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:53,548
We've grown apart,

416
00:20:53,619 --> 00:20:57,783
but l have no memory of us
ever thinking she hated us.

417
00:20:57,856 --> 00:20:59,221
Where is Heart?

418
00:20:59,491 --> 00:21:00,958
We need him in here.

419
00:21:01,026 --> 00:21:02,186
(Emotion)
<i> l'll handle this.</i>

420
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:08,158
Whoa.
Take it easy Emotion.

421
00:21:10,636 --> 00:21:12,604
This room looks like
a tornado ran through it.

422
00:21:12,671 --> 00:21:13,968
What happened in here?

423
00:21:14,039 --> 00:21:15,097
Nothing.

424
00:21:15,173 --> 00:21:16,731
l thought l heard some
arguing earlier.

425
00:21:16,808 --> 00:21:18,070
lt was nothing!

426
00:21:18,143 --> 00:21:19,735
What are you
keeping from me?

427
00:21:19,811 --> 00:21:22,143
What am l
keeping from you?

428
00:21:22,214 --> 00:21:23,704
What are you
keeping from me?

429
00:21:23,782 --> 00:21:26,182
Emotion, please.
Don't get carried away here!

430
00:21:26,251 --> 00:21:28,776
[Emotion chatters angrily
in the distance]

431
00:21:28,854 --> 00:21:31,652
[door opens]

432
00:21:33,091 --> 00:21:37,152
[suspenseful music]

433
00:21:43,235 --> 00:21:46,136
(Emotion) That l'm a failure,
<i>is that what you want me to say? </i>

434
00:21:46,204 --> 00:21:48,172
Mind, Will,
go get Heart.

435
00:21:52,911 --> 00:21:54,139
Here, l'll take care
of this.

436
00:21:54,212 --> 00:21:55,110
Shut up, Mind!

437
00:21:55,947 --> 00:21:58,211
Michael, did you
hear what l said?

438
00:21:59,718 --> 00:22:01,549
You never
listen to me.

439
00:22:01,620 --> 00:22:02,814
Just drop it.
All right? l'm fine.

440
00:22:02,888 --> 00:22:03,650
Obviously not!

441
00:22:03,722 --> 00:22:07,954
They cancelled my strip.
Ok?

442
00:22:08,026 --> 00:22:10,756
lt's over.
l'm finished.

443
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:11,818
l'm sorry.

444
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:18,233
So, what are you
going to do now?

445
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:22,800
l don't know,
maybe l'll go draw a sign

446
00:22:22,874 --> 00:22:24,068
and panhandle
by the interstate.

447
00:22:24,142 --> 00:22:24,631
How about that?

448
00:22:24,710 --> 00:22:25,972
Look, l know
you're upset,

449
00:22:26,044 --> 00:22:28,069
but you don't have to get
sarcastic with me.

450
00:22:28,146 --> 00:22:29,909
l guess your parents
were right about me.

451
00:22:29,981 --> 00:22:31,278
You know what l came
in here to talk to you,

452
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:33,944
but obviously this
is the wrong time.

453
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:36,010
Let's be honest, you never
respected what l do.

454
00:22:36,088 --> 00:22:37,919
We are not going
to do this right now.

455
00:22:37,989 --> 00:22:39,616
l get emails from
complete strangers

456
00:22:39,691 --> 00:22:41,181
who are more supportive
than my own wife.

457
00:22:41,259 --> 00:22:43,250
Well excuse me if l don't
meet your expectations.

458
00:22:44,930 --> 00:22:45,555
What's going on?

459
00:22:45,630 --> 00:22:46,790
( Amy)
<i> What is it Michael? </i>

460
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:48,093
Heart!

461
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:49,030
Oh, please.

462
00:22:49,101 --> 00:22:52,628
l have sacrificed for you so
you could live your dream.

463
00:22:52,704 --> 00:22:53,966
And when l needed you,
Michael,

464
00:22:54,039 --> 00:22:56,269
all you did this past year
was lock me out!

465
00:22:56,341 --> 00:23:00,277
[Amy continues to talk]

466
00:23:00,345 --> 00:23:01,573
Vines!

467
00:23:01,646 --> 00:23:02,738
(Heart) <i> Move!</i>
<i>Conscience!  Move!</i>

468
00:23:02,814 --> 00:23:04,611
(Michael) <i> l sacrifice</i>
<i>for  you every  day!</i>

469
00:23:04,683 --> 00:23:05,911
What's the thanks l get?

470
00:23:05,984 --> 00:23:08,817
You ignore me
when l talk to you.

471
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:10,787
And then you jump down
<i>my throat for no reason? </i>

472
00:23:10,856 --> 00:23:13,017
(Michael)
<i> Absolutely nothing!</i>

473
00:23:13,091 --> 00:23:16,788
( Amy) l don't understand this
<i>has been going on for years.</i>

474
00:23:16,862 --> 00:23:18,352
[slam against door]

475
00:23:20,332 --> 00:23:22,926
l'm not going
to take it anymore.

476
00:23:24,069 --> 00:23:25,331
(Emotion) Not gonna
<i>take it anymore? </i>

477
00:23:25,404 --> 00:23:26,803
[boom]

478
00:23:26,872 --> 00:23:27,930
(Emotion) <i> Maybe if </i>
<i> you acted  your age,</i>

479
00:23:28,006 --> 00:23:29,837
l wouldn't have to treat
<i> you like a five year old.</i>

480
00:23:29,908 --> 00:23:31,307
l mean give me a breakl

481
00:23:31,376 --> 00:23:33,776
[boom]

482
00:23:33,845 --> 00:23:35,938
(Emotion) <i>Get out!</i>
<i>Get out of  my life</i>!

483
00:23:36,014 --> 00:23:37,914
What have you done?
Stop!

484
00:23:37,983 --> 00:23:40,213
(Emotion)
<i>Just get out!</i>

485
00:23:43,822 --> 00:23:45,153
Memory!
Snap out of it!

486
00:23:54,966 --> 00:23:56,228
Amy, wait.

487
00:23:58,036 --> 00:23:58,764
l'm sorry.

488
00:24:00,705 --> 00:24:01,637
l don't know why
l said that.

489
00:24:03,041 --> 00:24:05,009
l just got angry and l said
some things l didn't mean.

490
00:24:05,076 --> 00:24:06,634
l'm sorry l took it
out on you.

491
00:24:08,947 --> 00:24:09,811
Can we please
just talk about this?

492
00:24:09,881 --> 00:24:11,644
There's nothing
more to talk about.

493
00:24:11,716 --> 00:24:12,876
l've got something
l want to say.

494
00:24:12,951 --> 00:24:14,179
l don't want
to hear it.

495
00:24:14,252 --> 00:24:15,150
l know l need
some help.

496
00:24:19,124 --> 00:24:20,716
l'm willing to go
to counseling.

497
00:24:20,792 --> 00:24:22,885
lt's too late
for that.

498
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:23,950
Amy, please.

499
00:24:24,029 --> 00:24:26,259
Honey,
look at me please.

500
00:24:26,331 --> 00:24:28,060
l just got upset about
the syndicate that's all, ok?

501
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:29,998
l'm sorry
l took it out on you.

502
00:24:33,705 --> 00:24:35,900
l love you.

503
00:24:39,744 --> 00:24:41,041
Do you still love me?

504
00:24:44,249 --> 00:24:46,376
l don't know what
l feel anymore.

505
00:24:51,256 --> 00:24:54,054
[crash!]

506
00:25:02,934 --> 00:25:07,837
[crying]

507
00:25:07,906 --> 00:25:09,271
Look what
you've done.

508
00:25:12,811 --> 00:25:14,779
l want her back.

509
00:25:20,852 --> 00:25:21,910
l want my wife back.

510
00:25:21,987 --> 00:25:31,419
[suspenseful music]

511
00:25:31,496 --> 00:25:35,057
(TV) <i>Foreign  Auto  Mart.</i>
Where no deal will be refused.

512
00:25:35,133 --> 00:25:36,293
(Weather Lady) What it's
<i>going to do is move slowly,</i>

513
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:37,027
[cellphone vibration]

514
00:25:37,102 --> 00:25:40,196
but it's also gonna dissipate as
<i>it comes into our viewing area.</i>

515
