We haven't slept in
the same room...

773
00:39:22,827 --> 00:39:24,556
Heart.

774
00:39:24,628 --> 00:39:27,893
There's no use
fighting it anymore.

775
00:39:27,965 --> 00:39:29,159
Fighting what?

776
00:39:29,233 --> 00:39:32,134
The inevitable.
lt's over.

777
00:39:32,203 --> 00:39:33,295
Don't listen
to him Heart.

778
00:39:33,371 --> 00:39:36,169
Shut up Conscience.

779
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:38,003
This is what
l warned you about.

780
00:39:38,075 --> 00:39:40,566
Every one of us is being
motivated by fear.

781
00:39:40,644 --> 00:39:41,804
That's ridiculous.

782
00:39:41,879 --> 00:39:43,039
l'm not afraid
of anything.

783
00:39:43,114 --> 00:39:44,081
You?

784
00:39:44,148 --> 00:39:46,275
You're the one who
fears the most.

785
00:39:46,350 --> 00:39:48,944
Oh, yeah?

786
00:39:49,019 --> 00:39:52,216
l'm not afraid of you,
you old bag of wind.

787
00:39:52,289 --> 00:39:54,655
You want to see
some rage?

788
00:39:54,725 --> 00:39:56,022
Just keep it up
Lady Justice.

789
00:39:56,093 --> 00:39:58,220
l don't know what this
has to do with anything.

790
00:39:58,295 --> 00:40:00,024
Wait.

791
00:40:00,097 --> 00:40:02,156
Conscience is right.

792
00:40:02,233 --> 00:40:03,359
Mind,
it's obvious to me

793
00:40:03,634 --> 00:40:06,125
that fear has changed
your way of thinking.

794
00:40:06,203 --> 00:40:08,228
So how do
we fight it?

795
00:40:08,305 --> 00:40:11,001
With perfect love.

796
00:40:11,075 --> 00:40:12,633
What?

797
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:14,701
Perfect love.

798
00:40:14,779 --> 00:40:17,680
Love that drives a wedge
between you and your wife.

799
00:40:17,748 --> 00:40:20,342
Love that steals
your dream job.

800
00:40:20,418 --> 00:40:23,114
Love that buries
your child.

801
00:40:23,187 --> 00:40:24,711
Mind!

802
00:40:24,789 --> 00:40:26,950
Do you hear what
you're saying?

803
00:40:27,024 --> 00:40:29,219
You are the one that
taught us the truth.

804
00:40:29,293 --> 00:40:30,851
And now you're
believing lies.

805
00:40:30,928 --> 00:40:32,691
l've had enough!

806
00:40:32,763 --> 00:40:34,856
l can't stand
this anymore.

807
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:38,231
Conscience,
one more word.

808
00:40:38,302 --> 00:40:40,236
Silence.

809
00:40:40,304 --> 00:40:42,101
That's the word.

810
00:40:42,173 --> 00:40:43,333
[suspenseful music]
[fighting sounds]

811
00:41:51,275 --> 00:41:52,765
What's gotten us
to the point

812
00:41:52,843 --> 00:41:55,141
that we are destroying
each other.

813
00:41:55,212 --> 00:41:57,112
We chose to follow Him.

814
00:41:57,181 --> 00:41:59,411
And the consequences haven't
been very good, now have they?

815
00:41:59,483 --> 00:42:01,917
Mind, remember why
we followed Him.

816
00:42:01,986 --> 00:42:03,146
You were convinced
by the --

817
00:42:03,220 --> 00:42:04,778
(Mind)
<i>Reason.</i>

818
00:42:04,855 --> 00:42:07,346
lt <i>was reasonable to</i>
<i>believe the  Word of  God</i>

819
00:42:07,424 --> 00:42:11,360
because the evidence could
not be explained away.

820
00:42:11,428 --> 00:42:13,123
ln the same way
it was reasonable

821
00:42:13,197 --> 00:42:15,961
to focus our career
on cartooning.

822
00:42:16,033 --> 00:42:19,002
That's our skill
and interest.

823
00:42:19,069 --> 00:42:21,094
lt was reasonable
to marry Amy.

824
00:42:21,171 --> 00:42:23,867
She is beautiful.

825
00:42:23,941 --> 00:42:26,307
We have a lot in common, and
from the first time we say her

826
00:42:26,377 --> 00:42:28,504
we desired to spend
our life with her.

827
00:42:28,779 --> 00:42:33,011
All of our choices have
been based on reason.

828
00:42:33,083 --> 00:42:36,177
And so l'm
asking you Heart.

829
00:42:36,253 --> 00:42:39,848
What is the reasonable
thing for us to do?

830
00:42:39,924 --> 00:42:42,859
Should we continue in
an unhappy marriage?

831
00:42:42,927 --> 00:42:46,886
Following a God who took away
everything that matters to us?

832
00:42:46,964 --> 00:42:50,525
Or isn't it reasonable
to give Amy her freedom

833
00:42:50,801 --> 00:42:53,531
and start over
<i>in a new place? </i>

834
00:42:58,542 --> 00:43:00,339
When was the last time
you were in there?

835
00:43:05,883 --> 00:43:09,876
These vines -- our old nature,
they've corrupted Mind

836
00:43:09,954 --> 00:43:11,285
and poisoned
he rest of us.

837
00:43:14,258 --> 00:43:16,317
You can't fight
those three alone.

838
00:43:16,393 --> 00:43:18,418
You know that
don't you?

839
00:43:18,495 --> 00:43:22,295
You've become weak
and they've become strong.

840
00:43:24,034 --> 00:43:25,558
Their arguments
may seem persuasive

841
00:43:25,836 --> 00:43:27,235
but there's
no truth in them.

842
00:43:32,009 --> 00:43:35,001
Why couldn't you find
the memory of our first love?

843
00:43:35,079 --> 00:43:37,240
lt's not where it's
supposed to be, all right?

844
00:43:37,314 --> 00:43:38,872
How can that be?

845
00:43:38,949 --> 00:43:41,315
Someone must
have taken it.

846
00:43:41,385 --> 00:43:42,943
But why?

847
00:43:43,020 --> 00:43:46,478
Those three have lost
faith in God and in you.

848
00:43:46,557 --> 00:43:49,253
They are afraid of the future
so they've taken over.

849
00:43:49,326 --> 00:43:53,126
Heart, finding that memory
is everything.

850
00:43:55,165 --> 00:43:58,464
Emotion....

851
00:43:58,535 --> 00:44:02,062
He has a memory orb.
l saw it.

852
00:44:02,139 --> 00:44:05,438
Will must have
put him up to it.

853
00:44:05,509 --> 00:44:06,533
(Memory)
<i> Will? </i>

854
00:44:08,145 --> 00:44:11,512
l caught him coming out
of your chamber.

855
00:44:11,582 --> 00:44:13,846
He's orchestrated
all of this.

856
00:44:13,917 --> 00:44:16,249
You have to
get it back.

857
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:20,222
Conscience.
Go to Will's Domain.

858
00:44:20,290 --> 00:44:22,884
Make sure he hasn't
taken the memory.

859
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:25,451
Try to talk some
sense into him.

860
00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:31,031
l'll take care
of Emotion.

861
00:44:34,505 --> 00:44:35,938
You come
with me.

862
00:44:36,006 --> 00:44:37,064
Wait.

863
00:44:39,276 --> 00:44:43,940
Remember no matter what
happens to me, don't give up.

864
00:44:44,014 --> 00:44:48,451
When you find it, you must
repent and return to Him.

865
00:44:48,519 --> 00:44:50,077
His power will
overcome them.

866
00:44:50,154 --> 00:45:00,394
[suspenseful music]

867
00:45:08,005 --> 00:45:09,563
Will?

868
00:45:11,942 --> 00:45:17,608
[crying]

869
00:45:22,186 --> 00:45:25,155
What are you
doing here?

870
00:45:25,222 --> 00:45:29,955
Uh, we've come
for the memory?

871
00:45:41,071 --> 00:45:43,039
Are you lost,
Conscience?

872
00:45:46,009 --> 00:45:48,273
You know
why l'm here.

873
00:45:48,345 --> 00:45:51,371
You've come to join
forces with me.

874
00:45:51,448 --> 00:45:52,540
Very funny.

875
00:45:52,616 --> 00:45:54,675
Now give me
what l want.

876
00:45:54,752 --> 00:45:56,344
You can't have it.

877
00:45:56,420 --> 00:45:57,614
Why not?

878
00:45:57,688 --> 00:45:59,417
Because l have
to hold on to this.

879
00:45:59,490 --> 00:46:02,550
lt's all l have left.

880
00:46:02,626 --> 00:46:05,151
You and Heart
have already lost.

881
00:46:05,229 --> 00:46:06,025
That's not true.

882
00:46:06,096 --> 00:46:07,222
The decision has
been made.

883
00:46:07,297 --> 00:46:08,264
Not by all of us!

884
00:46:08,332 --> 00:46:09,526
The majority rules.

885
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:12,398
l know right
from wrong.

886
00:46:12,469 --> 00:46:13,527
And what you're
doing is wrong.

887
00:46:16,273 --> 00:46:18,969
But it's not as black
and white as you think.

888
00:46:19,042 --> 00:46:20,509
Don't make me
take it from you.

889
00:46:20,577 --> 00:46:24,240
[laughing]

890
00:46:26,750 --> 00:46:34,589
No, Heart.
You're too weak.

891
00:46:34,658 --> 00:46:43,498
[suspenseful music]
[fighting noise]

892
00:46:43,567 --> 00:46:47,059
[laughing]

893
00:46:47,137 --> 00:46:49,162
Memory, focus.

894
00:46:49,239 --> 00:47:01,208
[suspenseful music]
[fighting noise]

895
00:47:01,285 --> 00:47:02,047
Stop it!

896
00:47:02,119 --> 00:47:03,245
You leave him
alone right now.

897
00:47:03,554 --> 00:47:04,714
Memory!

898
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:17,396
[yelling]

899
00:47:17,467 --> 00:47:49,825
[suspenseful music]
[fighting noise]

900
00:47:49,867 --> 00:47:51,391
Stop it.
Listen to me!

901
00:47:51,468 --> 00:47:53,163
Don't do this!
Will, stop!

902
00:47:53,237 --> 00:47:56,206
l'm helping you see
things our way.

903
00:47:58,108 --> 00:47:59,507
You know this
is wrong.

904
00:47:59,576 --> 00:48:00,338
[mumbling]

905
00:48:01,445 --> 00:48:04,141
l want what's
best for Heart.

906
00:48:04,214 --> 00:48:06,808
You must
believe that.

907
00:48:08,752 --> 00:48:09,776
Don't do this.

908
00:48:09,853 --> 00:48:12,617
Will...
Listen to me!

909
00:48:12,689 --> 00:48:18,719
[suspenseful music]

910
00:48:18,795 --> 00:48:42,312
[yelling]
[suspenseful music]

911
00:48:58,735 --> 00:49:00,566
lt's not
the right one.

912
00:49:00,637 --> 00:49:02,434
What?

913
00:49:02,506 --> 00:49:04,440
lt has to be.

914
00:49:05,676 --> 00:49:06,870
lt's not.

915
00:49:06,944 --> 00:49:08,172
Show me.

916
00:49:10,647 --> 00:49:12,239
Show me!

917
00:49:13,550 --> 00:49:15,142
l want to go alone.

918
00:49:19,323 --> 00:49:20,255
[swoosh]

919
00:49:20,324 --> 00:49:22,258
(Doctor) <i> Amy, come on.</i>
<i> You can do this.</i>

920
00:49:22,326 --> 00:49:23,190
We are getting
to the end.

921
00:49:23,260 --> 00:49:23,783
You're doing great.

922
00:49:23,860 --> 00:49:25,259
Ready and push!

923
00:49:25,329 --> 00:49:26,159
Focus!

924
00:49:26,229 --> 00:49:28,823
Two, Three,
Four, Five!

925
00:49:28,899 --> 00:49:29,888
Great!
Great job!

926
00:49:31,335 --> 00:49:32,165
You can do
this, ok?

927
00:49:32,235 --> 00:49:33,361
Come on Amy!

928
00:49:33,437 --> 00:49:34,426
Four, Five, Six.

929
00:49:34,504 --> 00:49:35,300
[baby crying]

930
00:49:35,372 --> 00:49:37,465
(Doctor) <i>There  you go.</i>
<i>Go, Go, Go! That's it!</i>

931
00:49:37,541 --> 00:49:40,806
Oh, it's a beautiful girll

932
00:49:40,877 --> 00:49:41,809
Ellie!

933
00:49:41,878 --> 00:49:43,743
[laughing]

934
00:49:44,982 --> 00:49:46,472
You did it!

935
00:49:46,550 --> 00:49:47,278
Oh, Ellie!

936
00:49:47,351 --> 00:49:49,546
She's here!
You talking to me?

937
00:49:49,619 --> 00:49:53,817
[Michael and Amy talking]

938
00:49:59,830 --> 00:50:02,697
[swoosh]

939
00:50:09,806 --> 00:50:21,980
[Crying]

940
00:50:22,252 --> 00:50:24,720
l'm sorry.

941
00:50:30,594 --> 00:50:32,789
(Conscience)
<i>Nooooooooo!</i>

942
00:50:36,466 --> 00:50:39,333
[door opens]

943
00:50:41,004 --> 00:50:42,301
Will?

944
00:50:45,275 --> 00:50:46,572
Release him.

945
00:50:49,913 --> 00:50:51,642
l said release him!

946
00:50:57,020 --> 00:50:59,386
Conscience.

947
00:50:59,456 --> 00:51:00,582
What should l do?

948
00:51:01,992 --> 00:51:04,256
(Mind)
Choose reason.

949
00:51:04,528 --> 00:51:08,464
Should we continue in
an unhappy marriage.

950
00:51:08,532 --> 00:51:10,022
Following a God --

951
00:51:10,300 --> 00:51:13,394
Who took away everything
that matters to us.

952
00:51:13,470 --> 00:51:20,034
Yes... Or is it reasonable
to give Amy her freedom.

953
00:51:20,310 --> 00:51:21,299
And start over.

954
00:51:21,378 --> 00:51:58,515
[suspenseful music]

955
00:51:58,548 --> 00:52:01,813
No! No! No!

956
00:52:01,885 --> 00:52:22,000
[suspenseful music]

957
00:52:22,706 --> 00:52:23,331
(Michael)
<i> All l said was...</i>

958
00:52:23,406 --> 00:52:24,338
( Amy) <i>That  you don't</i>
<i>think   l'm a Christian.</i>

959
00:52:24,407 --> 00:52:25,431
l didn't say that.

960
00:52:25,509 --> 00:52:26,100
Daddy.

961
00:52:26,376 --> 00:52:26,933
Mommy.

962
00:52:27,010 --> 00:52:31,947
Ellie not now.
Don't interrupt.

963
00:52:32,015 --> 00:52:34,950
Look, honey l'm sorry
l upset you.

964
00:52:35,018 --> 00:52:36,713
l love you.

965
00:52:36,786 --> 00:52:38,686
l'm just concerned
about your faith.

966
00:52:38,755 --> 00:52:41,849
Why don't you
believe me? Ok?

967
00:52:41,925 --> 00:52:46,021
l told you l believe
in Jesus.

968
00:52:46,096 --> 00:52:47,529
(Michael)
<i> l know.</i>

969
00:52:47,597 --> 00:52:49,394
But the Jesus you believe
in doesn't exist.

970
00:52:49,466 --> 00:52:50,524
(Ellie) Mommy, l want
you to read this!

971
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:50,998
(Michael)
Ellie, sit down!

972
00:52:51,067 --> 00:52:51,726
(Amy)
Michael, stop!

973
00:52:51,801 --> 00:52:54,736
[crash]

974
00:53:06,783 --> 00:53:07,772
[car horn]

975
00:53:14,558 --> 00:53:14,887
[gasp]

976
00:53:30,740 --> 00:53:35,473
There's a cab
in front of the house.

977
00:53:35,545 --> 00:53:36,978
Where are
you going?

978
00:53:38,782 --> 00:53:39,806
l thought you'd left.

979
00:53:43,887 --> 00:53:45,047
You got the job.

980
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:55,027
Were you just going to
leave without telling me?

981
00:53:56,833 --> 00:53:57,800
Michael, look at me.

982
00:54:01,671 --> 00:54:04,105
Don't you think we should
have discussed this first?

983
00:54:04,174 --> 00:54:05,106
This affects me too --

984
00:54:05,175 --> 00:54:07,643
l don't have time
to talk right now.

985
00:54:07,711 --> 00:54:09,178
l've got to catch
a plane.

986
00:54:09,246 --> 00:54:10,110
l'll call you
from Connecticut.

987
00:54:10,180 --> 00:54:12,580
What are you saying,
Michael?

988
00:54:12,649 --> 00:54:15,516
Michael,
what about me?

989
00:54:15,585 --> 00:54:16,745
What about us?

990
00:54:16,820 --> 00:54:17,809
We'll talk
about it later.

991
00:54:17,887 --> 00:54:20,048
No, you are going
to tell me right now!

992
00:54:25,195 --> 00:54:27,459
l'm setting
you free.

993
00:54:27,530 --> 00:54:28,087
What does
that mean?

994
00:54:28,164 --> 00:54:29,756
You could have
studied in Paris.

995
00:54:29,833 --> 00:54:31,596
You could have
had a career

996
00:54:31,668 --> 00:54:33,693
but you sacrificed all
that to be my wife.

997
00:54:33,770 --> 00:54:34,566
That's ridiculous!

998
00:54:34,638 --> 00:54:36,128
l don't have to go
to Paris to paint!

999
00:54:37,707 --> 00:54:38,605
l became a teacher.

1000
00:54:38,675 --> 00:54:39,573
That was my choice!

1001
00:54:39,643 --> 00:54:42,168
How dare you decide
what is best for my life!

1002
00:54:42,245 --> 00:54:44,110
Would you just
look at us Amy!

1003
00:54:44,180 --> 00:54:45,738
Look at us!

1004
00:54:45,815 --> 00:54:49,012
We can't talk without it
turning into a battle.

1005
00:54:49,085 --> 00:54:50,017
So it's my fault.

1006
00:54:50,086 --> 00:54:53,146
No, it's my fault.

1007
00:54:56,960 --> 00:54:59,724
l just thought our lives would
be different, you know?

1008
00:55:02,165 --> 00:55:04,759
l prayed and prayed
and l thought that things

1009
00:55:04,834 --> 00:55:09,134
would get better but it's been
a year and nothing has changed.

1010
00:55:11,875 --> 00:55:13,172
l want us to be
happy again...

1011
00:55:13,243 --> 00:55:15,143
You mean l don't
make you happy.

1012
00:55:15,211 --> 00:55:16,678
l didn't say that.

1013
00:55:16,746 --> 00:55:18,611
l'm sorry if l don't
please you anymore.

1014
00:55:21,651 --> 00:55:25,781
So you are
giving up.

1015
00:55:25,855 --> 00:55:26,981
That's it?

1016
00:55:27,057 --> 00:55:27,921
Amy.

1017
00:55:27,991 --> 00:55:29,982
What?

1018
00:55:30,060 --> 00:55:31,584
You don't
understand do you?

1019
00:55:31,661 --> 00:55:34,653
What, because l don't go
to church with you

1020
00:55:34,731 --> 00:55:35,823
or because we don't
talk anymore--

1021
00:55:35,899 --> 00:55:36,866
That's not
the main reason --

1022
00:55:36,933 --> 00:55:38,025
What is
the main reason?

1023
00:55:38,101 --> 00:55:39,033
Tell me Michael!

1024
00:55:39,102 --> 00:55:40,228
lt's guilt!

1025
00:55:44,874 --> 00:55:45,966
Guilt, Amy.

1026
00:55:53,149 --> 00:55:56,880
l can't do
this anymore.

1027
00:55:56,953 --> 00:56:00,946
When l look at you,
l see Ellie.

1028
00:56:01,024 --> 00:56:04,016
And l'm reminded
of what l did,

1029
00:56:04,094 --> 00:56:06,562
and l know that you
blame me for what happened --

1030
00:56:06,629 --> 00:56:07,789
l never said
l blame you --

1031
00:56:07,864 --> 00:56:10,731
l blame myself!

1032
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:15,931
What?
What do you mean?

1033
00:56:16,005 --> 00:56:19,031
lf l would have just
stopped arguing with you.

1034
00:56:19,109 --> 00:56:22,135
lf l hadn't been following
that truck so closely.

1035
00:56:22,212 --> 00:56:23,839
lf l would just have been paying
more attention to the road.

1036
00:56:23,913 --> 00:56:26,780
lf l would have just let Ellie
give you that book!

1037
00:56:27,917 --> 00:56:30,317
She wouldn't have
unbuckled her seatbelt.

1038
00:56:32,722 --> 00:56:33,882
That stupid book.

1039
00:56:40,730 --> 00:56:43,631
l play it over and over again
in my head a thousand times

1040
00:56:43,700 --> 00:56:47,932
and every time l come
to the same conclusion.

1041
00:56:48,004 --> 00:56:50,700
l caused the death
of our daughter.

1042
00:56:50,774 --> 00:56:56,076
Stop...Stop.

1043
00:57:03,753 --> 00:57:06,119
l'm so sorry.

1044
00:57:06,189 --> 00:57:07,850
l'm sorry.

1045
00:57:07,924 --> 00:57:09,050
Michael.

1046
00:57:09,125 --> 00:57:12,720
Michael,
don't do this.

1047
00:57:12,796 --> 00:57:16,061
Don't give up
on me.

1048
00:57:19,803 --> 00:57:21,327
Don't give up
on us.

1049
00:57:25,942 --> 00:57:27,068
We used to be happy.

1050
00:57:31,381 --> 00:57:32,939
Do you remember that?

1051
00:57:35,251 --> 00:57:38,743
All that changed when l started
pushing my faith on you.

1052
00:57:41,858 --> 00:57:43,086
l made a mistake.

1053
00:57:47,330 --> 00:57:49,355
And some mistakes you
never stop paying for.

1054
00:57:55,905 --> 00:57:56,929
l got to go.

1055
00:57:58,775 --> 00:58:01,175
No! No!

1056
00:58:01,244 --> 00:58:06,011
Michael!

1057
00:58:06,082 --> 00:58:12,954
[crying]
[suspenseful music]

1058
00:58:13,022 --> 00:58:16,458
(Ray) <i> Where is Ellie</i>
<i>right now? </i>

1059
00:58:19,062 --> 00:58:20,825
Heaven.

1060
00:58:20,897 --> 00:58:22,125
Do you believe that?

1061
00:58:27,036 --> 00:58:29,903
When is God
most glorified?

1062
00:58:29,973 --> 00:58:34,433
When things are easy
or when things become hard?

1063
00:58:34,511 --> 00:58:36,445
And through the deepest
grief and agony

1064
00:58:36,513 --> 00:58:38,481
we find the supernatural
strength to say,

1065
00:58:38,748 --> 00:58:42,912
''God is all l need.''

1066
00:58:42,986 --> 00:58:44,112
God is my life.

1067
00:58:44,187 --> 00:58:46,018
He's who l live for.

1068
00:58:46,089 --> 00:58:48,785
And He's good.

1069
00:58:48,858 --> 00:58:51,986
Man, once you get that life
seems to make sense.

1070
00:58:53,062 --> 00:58:56,828
Because this world,
this is not our home.

1071
00:58:56,900 --> 00:59:01,428
We are passing through a broken
world that is not our home.

1072
00:59:03,106 --> 00:59:07,440
But Ellie -- she's at home
right now with Him.

1073
00:59:07,510 --> 00:59:10,070
Now, do you
believe that?

1074
00:59:10,146 --> 00:59:11,272
Yes, l believe that.

1075
00:59:14,817 --> 00:59:17,809
But you don't have any idea
what it's like.

1076
00:59:17,887 --> 00:59:20,788
A parent should never
have to bury their child.

1077
00:59:20,857 --> 00:59:22,290
Michael.

1078
00:59:22,358 --> 00:59:26,192
Ellie has never been more
alive than she is right now,

1079
00:59:26,262 --> 00:59:27,786
in the presence
of Jesus Christ.

1080
00:59:29,566 --> 00:59:30,863
l mean you got
to ask yourself,

1081
00:59:30,934 --> 00:59:33,402
if you could bring her
back right now.

1082
00:59:33,469 --> 00:59:35,096
Take her away from Him.

1083
00:59:35,171 --> 00:59:38,197
Take her away from her perfect
home and bring her back

1084
00:59:38,274 --> 00:59:42,335
to this sin-infested world,
would you?

1085
00:59:45,582 --> 00:59:47,106
No.

1086
00:59:47,183 --> 00:59:48,480
Now, look.

1087
00:59:48,551 --> 00:59:51,486
We're all
going to die.

1088
00:59:51,554 --> 00:59:57,424
And the only difference between
you and me is that l know when.

1089
01:00:00,229 --> 01:00:03,130
What are you
talking about?

1090
01:00:03,199 --> 01:00:06,930
l have cancer
and the doctors say

1091
01:00:07,003 --> 01:00:08,436
there is nothing
they can do.

1092
01:00:08,504 --> 01:00:10,995
What?

1093
01:00:11,074 --> 01:00:13,565
How long?

1094
01:00:13,843 --> 01:00:15,572
They're not sure.

1095
01:00:15,845 --> 01:00:18,143
But it's not as long
as l hoped for.

1096
01:00:22,485 --> 01:00:23,383
l'm so sorry.

1097
01:00:23,453 --> 01:00:24,351
Well, don't be.

1098
01:00:24,420 --> 01:00:30,825
Like l said before,
this is not my home.

1099
01:00:30,893 --> 01:00:32,019
How can you
think like that?

1100
01:00:32,095 --> 01:00:37,397
Everybody wants to go to heaven,
but nobody wants to die.

1101
01:00:37,467 --> 01:00:38,456
Look man.

1102
01:00:38,534 --> 01:00:42,265
When l first found out,
l was angry.

1103
01:00:42,338 --> 01:00:44,966
l couldn't help
but to think, ''why me?''

1104
01:00:45,041 --> 01:00:47,441
''Why now?''

1105
01:00:47,510 --> 01:00:50,479
But then l remembered
why Jesus died for me.

1106
01:00:50,546 --> 01:00:56,974
When l got that, it's like
the peace of God fell on me

1107
01:00:57,053 --> 01:01:01,513
like a summer rain.

1108
01:01:01,591 --> 01:01:04,890
You know, all this stuff l was
hanging onto in this world,

1109
01:01:04,961 --> 01:01:09,159
suddenly it has no meaning.

1110
01:01:09,232 --> 01:01:10,563
lt's amazing how the value
of stuff changes

1111
01:01:10,633 --> 01:01:13,158
when you are dying.

1112
01:01:13,236 --> 01:01:18,173
So you want to know peace,
know where you are going.

1113
01:01:18,341 --> 01:01:19,933
[intercom announcement]

1114
01:01:20,009 --> 01:01:23,035
That's my flight.

1115
01:01:25,281 --> 01:01:27,146
Where you headed?

1116
01:01:27,483 --> 01:01:29,007
[intercom announcement]

1117
01:01:29,085 --> 01:01:31,952
Home.

1118
01:01:33,089 --> 01:01:34,078
Thanks man.

1119
01:01:34,157 --> 01:01:35,351
l appreciate it.

1120
01:01:35,425 --> 01:01:37,256
You're welcome.

1121
01:01:37,326 --> 01:01:38,987
Come on guys.

1122
01:01:44,500 --> 01:01:56,469
[engine noise]

1123
01:01:56,546 --> 01:01:58,605
(Girl) <i>Give me one good</i>
son why   you are doing th

1124
01:01:58,681 --> 01:02:01,650
l just don't understand
<i>what the big deal is.</i>

1125
01:02:01,718 --> 01:02:05,552
But this is so unfair.

1126
01:02:05,621 --> 01:02:07,418
No, don't put Dad on.

1127
01:02:07,490 --> 01:02:10,118
Ok, here she is.

1128
01:02:10,193 --> 01:02:12,058
lt's Dad.

1129
01:02:12,128 --> 01:02:13,390
Hi, Daddy!

1130
01:02:18,701 --> 01:02:22,000
(Ellie) <i>Daddy, why </i>
<i>are  you leaving me? </i>

1131
01:02:26,709 --> 01:02:28,370
lt's for
the best honey.

1132
01:02:28,444 --> 01:02:30,469
Did l do
something wrong?

1133
01:02:30,546 --> 01:02:32,070
No.

1134
01:02:32,148 --> 01:02:34,582
No, sweetheart.

1135
01:02:34,650 --> 01:02:40,054
Then stay!
Stay with me!

1136
01:02:40,123 --> 01:02:41,715
l can't.

1137
01:02:45,528 --> 01:02:48,326
l have to
let you go.

1138
01:02:51,367 --> 01:02:55,531
l can't take you with me
because it's too painful.

1139
01:02:58,674 --> 01:03:00,642
l have to
start over.

1140
01:03:00,710 --> 01:03:02,610
But l'll see you
again, right?

1141
01:03:07,150 --> 01:03:08,378
l don't know.

1142
01:03:08,451 --> 01:03:09,679
What do you mean?

1143
01:03:11,354 --> 01:03:14,755
l lost something.

1144
01:03:15,024 --> 01:03:16,252
And l don't know
where it is.

1145
01:03:16,325 --> 01:03:18,020
What did you lose?

1146
01:03:20,096 --> 01:03:22,291
l guess l lost
my faith.

1147
01:03:22,365 --> 01:03:25,061
But Daddy, you told me
you can't lose your faith

1148
01:03:25,134 --> 01:03:28,126
because it always
leaves a sign.

1149
01:03:28,204 --> 01:03:29,432
She said she believes.

1150
01:03:29,505 --> 01:03:30,995
She believes up here.

1151
01:03:31,073 --> 01:03:33,200
We just need to pray
that she believes in here.

1152
01:03:33,276 --> 01:03:37,212
You see, true faith
always leaves a sign.

1153
01:03:37,280 --> 01:03:40,181
You said faith is never
alone, it's always --

1154
01:03:40,249 --> 01:03:43,241
accompanied by works.

1155
01:03:43,319 --> 01:03:45,446
lt leaves signs.

1156
01:03:45,521 --> 01:03:47,489
That's it.

1157
01:03:55,364 --> 01:03:57,229
(Memory)
<i>Oh, where did it go? </i>

1158
01:03:57,300 --> 01:03:58,267
l know it was here.

1159
01:03:58,334 --> 01:04:00,268
Why can't l find it?

1160
01:04:00,336 --> 01:04:02,429
Memory.

1161
01:04:02,505 --> 01:04:04,268
The moment we
exercised faith.

1162
01:04:04,340 --> 01:04:05,204
lt's gone.

1163
01:04:05,274 --> 01:04:06,741
lt's not gone.

1164
01:04:06,809 --> 01:04:09,369
lt leaves traces
and that will lead us

1165
01:04:09,445 --> 01:04:10,571
to where our faith
is hidden.

1166
01:04:10,646 --> 01:04:12,273
l just don't
understand.

1167
01:04:12,348 --> 01:04:14,578
lt should be
right here.

1168
01:04:23,860 --> 01:04:30,595
[boom]

1169
01:04:30,666 --> 01:04:31,690
What is it?

1170
01:04:37,607 --> 01:04:39,131
Heart?

1171
01:04:39,208 --> 01:04:40,436
Where are you
going?

1172
01:04:40,509 --> 01:04:42,067
What happened?

1173
01:04:42,144 --> 01:04:56,081
[music]

1174
01:04:56,158 --> 01:04:57,386
What are you
looking for?

1175
01:05:00,563 --> 01:05:01,655
Where did you
hide it?

1176
01:05:02,365 --> 01:05:03,696
Hide what?

1177
01:05:03,766 --> 01:05:06,428
l don't know what
you are talking about.

1178
01:05:06,502 --> 01:05:07,730
l think you do.

1179
01:05:09,472 --> 01:05:14,739
You have the advantage now,
but not for long.

1180
01:05:14,810 --> 01:05:16,869
l wouldn't do that
if l were you.

1181
01:05:17,146 --> 01:05:18,306
What?

1182
01:05:23,252 --> 01:05:25,220
Heart.

1183
01:05:25,288 --> 01:05:27,848
You can't change
the will of the majority.

1184
01:05:27,924 --> 01:05:30,358
Now, stop
second guessing.

1185
01:05:30,426 --> 01:05:32,690
The choice
has been made.

1186
01:05:34,864 --> 01:05:38,561
[suspenseful music]

1187
01:05:38,634 --> 01:05:39,566
Go find where Will's
hidden the memory.

1188
01:05:39,635 --> 01:05:40,761
Follow the trail!

1189
01:05:40,836 --> 01:05:51,235
[suspenseful music]
[fighting noise]

1190
01:05:51,314 --> 01:05:51,905
Glad you ladies
could be with us today.

1191
01:05:52,181 --> 01:06:05,754
[suspenseful music]
[fighting noise]

1192
01:06:05,828 --> 01:06:19,538
[suspenseful music]
[grunts]

1193
01:06:19,608 --> 01:06:20,836
(Michael) lf l just been paying
<i>more attention to the road</i>

1194
01:06:20,910 --> 01:06:23,208
lf l just let Ellie give
<i> you that book.</i>

1195
01:06:23,279 --> 01:06:25,304
That stupid book.

1196
01:06:25,448 --> 01:06:28,281
l caused the death
<i>of our daughter.</i>

1197
01:06:28,351 --> 01:06:29,511
( Amy)
<i> Michael.</i>

1198
01:06:29,585 --> 01:06:35,217
[music]

1199
01:06:35,291 --> 01:06:41,958
[grunts] [deep breathing]
[music]

1200
01:06:42,231 --> 01:07:35,581
[music]

1201
01:07:35,584 --> 01:07:38,485
[grunt]

1202
01:07:40,456 --> 01:08:21,222
[suspenseful music]

1203
01:08:45,654 --> 01:08:48,054
You're making
a big mistake.

1204
01:08:48,124 --> 01:08:50,820
l can't let you do what
you are about to do.

1205
01:08:50,893 --> 01:08:53,088
Choices have
consequences.

1206
01:08:53,362 --> 01:08:56,889
You don't have the authority
to make these decisions.

1207
01:08:56,966 --> 01:09:01,665
l'm not making
the decisions.

1208
01:09:05,441 --> 01:09:06,601
He is.

1209
01:09:08,978 --> 01:09:11,913
[boom]

1210
01:09:14,650 --> 01:09:17,084
This has gone
far enough.

1211
01:09:17,153 --> 01:09:19,553
What is he
talking about?

1212
01:09:19,622 --> 01:09:21,487
[boom]

1213
01:09:27,930 --> 01:09:28,988
lt was reasonable
for you to think that

1214
01:09:29,064 --> 01:09:30,691
Will had taken over.

1215
01:09:30,766 --> 01:09:35,465
But you and l both know, he only
does what the majority wants.

1216
01:09:39,074 --> 01:09:42,066
lt's time for you
to accept the truth.

1217
01:09:42,144 --> 01:09:44,135
l decide what
the majority wants now.

1218
01:09:52,087 --> 01:09:56,023
You have it,
don't you?

1219
01:09:56,091 --> 01:09:58,924
The memory you're
looking for?

1220
01:09:58,994 --> 01:10:00,859
Yes.

1221
01:10:00,930 --> 01:10:03,524
Mind, you're not
thinking clearly.

1222
01:10:03,599 --> 01:10:07,000
lf you'll only go back,
it will change everything.

1223
01:10:07,069 --> 01:10:08,934
No.

1224
01:10:09,004 --> 01:10:14,601
l've decided to move on,
but we have a problem.

1225
01:10:14,677 --> 01:10:17,942
You keep holding on
to the past,

1226
01:10:18,013 --> 01:10:20,846
and we can't live in
the past any longer.

1227
01:10:20,916 --> 01:10:25,751
Now, all l ask of you is
to submit to the majority.

1228
01:10:25,821 --> 01:10:28,915
l want you to bow
the knee.

1229
01:10:31,660 --> 01:10:32,718
Do it!

1230
01:10:40,502 --> 01:10:43,699
Will, it looks like Heart
needs some help.

1231
01:10:46,609 --> 01:10:47,837
There's no need
for that.

1232
01:10:48,711 --> 01:11:15,767
[music]

1233
01:11:15,804 --> 01:11:17,101
What happened
to you Mind?

1234
01:11:19,842 --> 01:11:20,968
What are you
afraid of?

1235
01:11:21,043 --> 01:11:22,806
l'm not afraid
of anything.

1236
01:11:22,878 --> 01:11:25,039
You are afraid
of loneliness.

1237
01:11:25,114 --> 01:11:28,174
Afraid of what
people will think.

1238
01:11:28,250 --> 01:11:30,650
You're afraid
of the future.

1239
01:11:30,719 --> 01:11:32,152
What?

1240
01:11:32,221 --> 01:11:33,688
Where is your faith?

1241
01:11:33,756 --> 01:11:35,053
Faith?

1242
01:11:35,124 --> 01:11:36,785
Faith in God?

1243
01:11:36,859 --> 01:11:40,989
Yes. The one
who created us.

1244
01:11:49,004 --> 01:11:50,665
You've forgotten
Him Mind.

1245
01:11:53,909 --> 01:11:56,503
You need
to remember.

1246
01:12:01,083 --> 01:12:03,813
l know what you're
trying to do Heart.

1247
01:12:03,886 --> 01:12:07,253
lt's not
going to work.

1248
01:12:07,323 --> 01:12:09,791
You can't
hide it forever.

1249
01:12:11,760 --> 01:12:14,695
lt's mine now.

1250
01:12:14,763 --> 01:12:16,788
You'll never
get it from me.

1251
01:12:16,865 --> 01:12:18,730
lt never belonged
to you.

1252
01:12:18,801 --> 01:12:21,133
l was the one who
researched the gospel.

1253
01:12:21,203 --> 01:12:24,730
l was the one who
was convinced.

1254
01:12:24,807 --> 01:12:27,640
l was the one who
made the decision.

1255
01:12:27,710 --> 01:12:29,940
Don't tell me that
it doesn't belong to me.

1256
01:12:30,012 --> 01:12:33,778
Simply knowing Jesus died
on a cross is not enough.

1257
01:12:33,849 --> 01:12:37,285
There's one thing you lack and
this is why you have doubts now.

1258
01:12:37,353 --> 01:12:41,187
This is what concerned
us about Amy.

1259
01:12:41,256 --> 01:12:42,621
The memory you're
holding is not yours

1260
01:12:42,691 --> 01:12:44,784
because He became
our first love

1261
01:12:44,860 --> 01:12:46,851
not believing a list
of historical facts.

1262
01:12:46,929 --> 01:12:48,897
All of us
were involved.

1263
01:12:50,366 --> 01:12:52,698
But this decision was
not yours to make.

1264
01:12:52,768 --> 01:12:55,202
Because this decision
was a matter --

1265
01:12:55,270 --> 01:12:55,929
Of the heart.

1266
01:13:07,750 --> 01:13:10,150
lt appears you are
no longer in the majority.

1267
01:13:13,389 --> 01:13:36,906
[suspenseful music]

1268
01:13:36,945 --> 01:13:37,639
Memory,
take them!

1269
01:13:37,713 --> 01:13:43,310
[suspenseful music]

1270
01:13:43,385 --> 01:13:47,082
[swoosh]

1271
01:13:47,156 --> 01:13:52,025
(Ray) Yeah, you're a good
person by the world's standards,

1272
01:13:52,094 --> 01:13:53,857
but not by God's.

1273
01:13:53,929 --> 01:13:55,726
Look, read it
for yourself.

1274
01:13:55,798 --> 01:13:58,198
''For the wages
of sin is death,

1275
01:13:58,267 --> 01:14:00,758
''but the gift of God
is eternal life

1276
01:14:00,836 --> 01:14:02,326
through Jesus
Christ our Lord.''

1277
01:14:02,404 --> 01:14:03,393
Look Michael.

1278
01:14:03,672 --> 01:14:05,731
l don't know what you've
done in your past.

1279
01:14:12,881 --> 01:14:15,782
Come on! Come on!
Come on! Let's go!

1280
01:14:19,021 --> 01:14:20,113
(Young Michael)
Go, go, go!

1281
01:14:20,189 --> 01:14:22,214
[car speeding off]

1282
01:14:22,291 --> 01:14:25,852
''But God demonstrates
his own love for us in this:

1283
01:14:25,928 --> 01:14:29,159
while we were still sinners,
Christ died for us.''

1284
01:14:29,231 --> 01:14:31,256
Sacrificial love.

1285
01:14:31,333 --> 01:14:33,893
You have a Heavenly Father
who loves you,

1286
01:14:33,969 --> 01:14:37,370
and He proved it by sending His
son to die for you.

1287
01:14:37,439 --> 01:14:39,202
(Emotion) <i> lt's all</i>
